                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002 Manchuria/90: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-22T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 22, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 22—7:32 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>689. Following from American Consul General at Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“June 21. Referring to my telegram of June 3, 5 p.m. and the published
                            declaration by Manchukuo of June 18th<note n="61" xml:id="d104fn61">For
                                text of declaration, see telegram No. 704, June 24, 1 p.m., from the
                                Minister in China, <ref target="#pg_104">p. 104</ref>.</note> [in]
                            which they propose the taking over [of] the customs in Manchuria and the
                            disruption of the existing administration unless Nanking agrees to hand
                            over the surplus revenue of all Manchurian customs stations, it is
                            understood that the remittance of Dairen customs funds to Shanghai was
                            stopped a few days ago. These funds are held in local banks as is the
                            case at Antung and Newchwang.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
